Title: Evolution as a design strategy for nonlinear architecture Generative modeling of 3-D surfaces  
Author: Una-May O'Reilly Girish Ramachandran 
Address: 545 Tech Sq Cambridge, MA, 02143  77 Mass Avenue Cambridge, MA 02139  
Affiliation: Artificial Intelligence Lab MIT  School of Architecture Massachusetts Institute of Technology  
Abstract: We discuss the dialogue between Architecture and Artificial Life. It takes place on the level of architectural reflection, process and tool development. We describe our investigative software, GGE Generative Genetic Explorer, in which genetic operations interact with AutoCAD to generate novel forms for the architect. GGE allows us to comment on design issues concerning computer aided design tools based on evolutionary algorithms. 
