Reference-contexts: There were slight difficulties with the architect tracking the actual transformation (i.e. what happened, to what, given the current form). We think one way to improve tracking is to provide labelling for a form's profiles and vertices in Auto CAD. Genotype coding: Following the genetic programming (GP) style <ref> (Koza 1992) </ref>, GGE does not encode the transformation sequence of the genotype into binary. A transformation is like a GP primitive (i.e. statement in a GP program). In contrast to GP, however, a transformation sequence is not encoded a tree structure for the purpose of crossover.
